"n.星座，星群 【英】 n. 星座，星群 (an arbitrary configuration of stars) 【考】 constellation : star / chord : note / queue : person(星星组成星座/音符 组成和音/人组成队伍) 【记】 con＋stell(星星)＋a tion→星星在一起→ 星座、星群 【同】 同根词：stellar(星 的，恒星的); interstellar(星际的) n. (88个象图形或图案的)星座, 星群; 群英荟萃 【根】con一起, stell星星－很多星星在—起－星座、星群 【参】stellar(adj 恒星的); interstellar(adj 星际的) 【类】constellation: star = chord: note = queue: person星座由星星组成 = 和音由音符组成 = 队伍由人组成 【记】stellar 恒星的 【相关】interstellar 星际的, quasi-stellar object 类星体 constellation (n.)  early 14c., from Old French constellacion ""constellation, conjuncture (of planets),"" from Late Latin constellationem (nominative constellatio) ""set with stars,"" from constellatus, from Latin com- ""with"" (see com-) + past participle of stellare ""to shine,"" from stella ""star"" (see star). Originally in astrology, of position of planets (""stars"") in regard to one another on a given day, usually one's birth day, as a determination of one's character. ""I folwed ay myn inclinacioun/By vertu of my constillacioun"" (Chaucer, ""Wife's Prologue,"" c.1386). Modern astronomical sense is from 1550s."
